  "text": "Corollary 1.6. Let X be a normal projective variety of Picard number two. Then: of Picard number two such that Aut(X) = Z/(2) * Z/(2) (a free product of two copies of Z/(2)) which contains Z as a subgroup of index two; see [CITATION_1] .",
